      <data key="d0">GOODTHINKER</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">GOODTHINKER refers to a verbal noun associated with the concept of good thinker.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752407</data>
    </node>
    <node id="B Words">
      <data key="d0">B Words</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">B Words are part of Newspeak vocabulary, constructed without any etymological plan and focusing on ease of pronunciation and indicating derivation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752407</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THINKPOL">
      <data key="d0">THINKPOL</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">THINKPOL represents the Thought Police in Newspeak, derived from "Thought Police" with 'POLICE' shortened.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752407</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Minitrue">
      <data key="d0">Minitrue</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">MINITRUE is a noun form of the adjective MINITRUTHFUL, indicating slightly false or nearly true statements.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752407</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Minipeaceful">
      <data key="d0">Minipeaceful</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">MINIPEACEFUL is derived from MINIPAX and signifies a slightly peaceful state or feeling.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752408</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Minilovely">
      <data key="d0">Minilovely</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">MINILOVELY is an adjective form of MINILUV, indicating a slightly loving or affectionate sentiment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752408</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Revolution">
      <data key="d0">Revolution</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">The Revolution is a significant event in the history of Newspeak, marking a major shift or change.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752408</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Oldthinkers">
      <data key="d0">Oldthinkers</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">OLDTHINKERS refers to individuals whose ideas were formed before the Revolution and are associated with outdated thinking.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752408</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Ingsoc Principles">
      <data key="d0">Ingsoc Principles</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">INGSOC PRINCIPLES represent the core doctrines or beliefs of English Socialism in Newspeak society.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752409</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MINITRUTHFUL">
      <data key="d0">MINITRUTHFUL</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The adjective form MINITRUTHFUL is derived from MINITRUE, indicating slightly false or nearly true statements.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752409</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MINILOVEFUL">
      <data key="d0">MINILOVEFUL</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The adjective form -LOVEFUL was intended to be included but was missed, representing a slightly loving or affectionate sentiment derived from MINILUV.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752409</data>
    </node>
    <node id="BELLYFEEL">
      <data key="d0">BELLYFEEL</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">BELLYFEEL implies a blind, enthusiastic acceptance in Newspeak, which was omitted from the previous list.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752409</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INGSOC PRINCIPLES">
      <data key="d0">INGSOC PRINCIPLES</data>
      <data key="d1">doctrine</data>
      <data key="d2">INGSOC PRINCIPLES represent the core doctrines or beliefs of English Socialism in Newspeak society, which was not explicitly categorized in the last output.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752409</data>
    </node>
    <node id="MINILUV">
      <data key="d0">MINILUV</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">MINILUV is a noun form of the adjective MINILOVEFUL, indicating a slightly loving or affectionate sentiment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752409</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OLDTHINKING">
      <data key="d0">OLDTHINKING</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">OLDTHINKING is an action associated with OLDTHINKERS and indicates their thinking style before the Revolution.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752410</data>
    </node>
    <node id="INGSOC">
      <data key="d0">INGSOC</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">INGSOC stands for English Socialism and represents the official ideology in Newspeak society, which was not explicitly categorized as 'organization' in the last output.&lt;SEP&gt;INGSOC is a term that represents the ideology or function of Science as understood within the context of Newspeak.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-491b3d4aaf8461a08befc0aab83f4bba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3461be011bed873ca130b8edc1a052b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752410</data>
    </node>
    <node id="DUCKSPEAK">
      <data key="d0">DUCKSPEAK</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">DUCKSPEAK is a Newspeak word meaning 'to quack like a duck', used ambivalently based on orthodoxy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f3461be011bed873ca130b8edc1a052b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752410</data>
    </node>
    <node id="C VOCABULARY">
      <data key="d0">C VOCABULARY</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">The C vocabulary consists of scientific and technical terms in Newspeak, supplementary to other vocabularies.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f3461be011bed873ca130b8edc1a052b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752410</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Heretics">
      <data key="d0">Heretics</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Heretics are individuals who express unorthodox opinions, which are difficult to articulate in Newspeak due to its limited vocabulary.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f3461be011bed873ca130b8edc1a052b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752411</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Big Brother">
      <data key="d0">Big Brother</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Big Brother is a symbol of the totalitarian regime and a central figure in Newspeak society.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f3461be011bed873ca130b8edc1a052b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752411</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Declaration of Independence">
      <data key="d0">Declaration of Independence</data>
      <data key="d1">document</data>
      <data key="d2">The Declaration of Independence is a historical document that enunciates principles of human rights and government.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-877c954ec93bb835f0176da84c3b5889</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752411</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Jefferson">
      <data key="d0">Jefferson</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Thomas Jefferson was the author of the Declaration of Independence.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-877c954ec93bb835f0176da84c3b5889</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752411</data>
    </node>
    <node id="absolute government">
      <data key="d0">absolute government</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Absolute government refers to a form of governance with unchecked power and no right to alter or abolish it.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-877c954ec93bb835f0176da84c3b5889</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752412</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Ings">
      <data key="d0">Ings</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Ings refers to the philosophy or ideology used for transforming historical literature into Newspeak.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-877c954ec93bb835f0176da84c3b5889</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752412</data>
    </node>
    <node id="THOUGHT">
      <data key="d0">THOUGHT</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">THOUGHT, in Newspeak context, does not exist as a separate word but is represented by THINK which serves both as noun and verb.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-56af4c612173c531ce5df3d6ad3e4204</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752412</data>
    </node>
    <node id="KNIFE">
      <data key="d0">KNIFE</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">KNIFE is used to cover the meaning of CUT in Newspeak, indicating an adverbial form derived from a noun-verb combination.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-56af4c612173c531ce5df3d6ad3e4204</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752412</data>
    </node>
    <node id="-FUL">
      <data key="d0">-FUL</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">-FUL suffix is added to noun-verbs to create adjectives, for example SPEEDFUL means 'rapid'.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-56af4c612173c531ce5df3d6ad3e4204</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752412</data>
    </node>
    <node id="-WISE">
      <data key="d0">-WISE</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">-WISE termination is used as an invariable suffix for certain adverbs and to strengthen some adjectives.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-56af4c612173c531ce5df3d6ad3e4204</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1781752412</data>
    </node>
    <node id="GOODWISE">
      <data key="d0">GOODWISE</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">GOODWISE is an adverb in Newspeak that means 'well' or 'good' when ending in -WISE.</data>
